          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "LCS"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Monochromatic  photon  beam  produced  at   the",
                " ROKK-1M  facility by Compton backscattering of laser",
                " light against high-energy electrons with E = 1.8 GeV",
                " circulating in the VEPP-4M storage ring."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "ESTRG"
                ],
                "institute": "4RUSSIB"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " ROKK-1M facility of BIMP, Novosibirsk."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Metalic foils  of  the  target  elements.  all target",
                " materials are of natural isotopic composition."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "SITA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " MACROFOL fission-track-etch detectors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The direct fission fragment track counting."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "To obtain the final values of the physical quantities",
                " and associated errors, the data have been treated by",
                " considering the statistics and efficiency  of  track",
                " counting (was estimated to be about 72 - 86 %).  The",
                " appropriate   corrections   for   both    gamma-beam",
                " attenuation  through  the stacks and self-absorption",
                " of fission fragments by  the  target  materials  for",
                " thinand thick-target geometry."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The  total - statistical   plus   systematic -",
                " errors are given."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-SYS",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Systematic errors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Photofission cross  sections   of   Bi-209,   Pb-nat,",
                " Au-197,  Pt-nat,  W-nat,  Ta-181,  V-51,  and Ti-nat",
                " nuclei have been measured  at  the  incident  photon",
                " energy   of  100  MeV  using  monochromatic  photons",
                " produced by compton backscattering  at  the  ROKK-1M",
                " facility in BIMP,  Novosibirsk. Detection of fission",
                " fragments has been performed by  means  of  MACROFOL",
                " track-etch  detectors  in close contact with metalic",
                " foils  of  the  target  elements.  The   values   of",
                " fissility  at  100 MeV deduced for the targets under",
                " investigation are found to range between 10**-4  and",
                " 10**-2.  The  present  results show consistency with",
                " the fissility trends calculated for 69 and  600  MeV",
                " monoenergetic photons using a formalism based on the",
                " current  two-step  model   for   intermediate-energy",
                " photofission reactions."
              ]
            }
          ],
